o assesses the impact of individual judges on Canadian society.This study examines the rhetoric of judicial expression in connection with a vast array of material on the subject of homosexuality. MacDougall's style is refreshingly conversational, and "Queer Judgments", with its critical perspective, celebrates the reforms that have been achieved and suggests strategies for social change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHomosexualityxLaw and legislationzCanada. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267894140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442678941423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442678941.jpg  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK